==English==

===Etymology===
From {{inh|en|enm|misheren}}, from {{inh|en|ang|mishȳran}}, {{m|ang|mishīeran|t=to hear amiss, not listen to, disobey}}, equivalent to {{prefix|en|mis|hear}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/mɪsˈhɪə(ɹ)/|lang=en}}
* {{rhymes|ɪə(ɹ)|lang=en}}

===Verb===
{{en-verb|mishears|mishearing|misheard}}

# {{lb|en|ambitransitive}} To [[hear]] [[wrongly]].
#: ''I '''misheard''' when she asked for mints, and gave her mince instead.''
# To [[misunderstand]]. {{rfex|lang=en}}

